cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

The paper discusses machine learning methods and neural networks, which are commonly associated with the computer science sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also addresses the challenge of implementing these methods on limited hardware resources, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach for low-bit precision quantization, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
